# Gforce API - Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.

```
# JWT secret - change this to a long random string in production
JWT_SECRET=change-me-to-a-long-random-string

# Office staff password
OFFICE_PASSWORD=office123

# GitHub PAT for database backup persistence across Render redeploys
# Needs: repo scope (for reading/writing to private repo)
# Without this, data is lost on every Render redeploy
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here

# SQLite database path (leave default)
DB_PATH=./gforce.db

# Port (default 3000, use PROCESS_ENV_PORT on Render)
PORT=3000
```

## Database Persistence

Render's free tier has ephemeral filesystem - data is lost on redeploy.
The `GITHUB_TOKEN` env var enables automatic backup to GitHub.
Generate a PAT at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
Scopes needed: `repo` (full private repo access)

## Adding Pilots

The database auto-seeds all 21 pilots on first run. If you need to add more:

```sql
-- Generate a PIN hash in Node:
-- require('bcryptjs').hashSync('PIN', 10)

INSERT INTO pilots (id, name, pin_hash, created_at) VALUES (
  lower(hex(randomblob(16))),
  'New Pilot Name',
  '$2a$10$YOUR_HASH',
  datetime('now')
);
```
